  "conclusion": "Replacing only the preceding c9 grouped-compact MoE path with selected_c1 while keeping the same c9 fixture and rowchunk2 full-attention did not reproduce the active-c2 [103,137] flake: five c9 selected_c1 rowchunk2 controls were [137]*9 and the five immediately following c2 default runs were all [137,137]. Compared with iter222, where red c9 grouped-compact rowchunk2 produced a c2 [103,137] flake in 1/3 cycles, the suspect narrows toward grouped-compact c9/red-path stress rather than high-row rowchunk2 alone. The result is still nondeterministic evidence, not proof of causality. No throughput claim is made.",
